{
  "texts": [
    "Centralized network architecture also makes the central server suffer from a heavy communication workload, calling for a decentralized server architecture [8].",
    "The third challenge is statistical heterogeneity.",
    "Aggregating clients' models together can result in a non-optimal combined model as client data is often non-IID (independent and identically distributed).",
    "Statistical heterogeneity introduces a degree of uncertainty into the learning model.",
    "Therefore, adopting the right aggregation and learning techniques is vital for robust implementation."
  ]
}